quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  4,27,"God wishes to turn towards you, but those who follow their lusts wish that ye should swerve with a mighty swerving"
  4,28,"God wishes to make it light for you, for man was created weak"
  4,29,"O ye who believe! devour not your property amongst yourselves vainly, unless it be a merchandise by mutual consent. And do not kill yourselves; verily, God is compassionate unto you"
  4,30,"But whoso does that maliciously and unjustly, we will broil him with fire; for that is easy with God"
  4,31,"If ye avoid great sins from which ye are forbidden, we will cover your offences and make you enter with a noble entrance"
  4,32,"And do not covet that by which God has preferred one of you over another. The men shall have a portion of what they earn, and the women a portion of what they earn; ask God for His grace, verily, God knows all"
  4,33,"To every one have we appointed kinsfolk as heirs of what parents and relatives and those with whom ye have joined right hands leave; so give them their portion, for, verily, God is over all a witness"